<TITLE> Wazed Miah's 1st death anniv today </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)  Today is the first death anniversary of Dr Wazed Miah, eminent nuclear scientist and husband of prime minister Sheikh Hasina. He died in the capital's Square Hospital on this day last year after suffering from a number of diseases including blood pressure, complexity in kidney and lungs, and diabetes. Different organisations have chalked out programmes to mark the day including discussion sessions commemorating his life and works and offering prayers. The Bangabandhu Academy organised a meeting at the National Press Club at 10:30am. Textile minister Abdul Latif Siddiqui, state minister for home Shamsul Haq Tuku, state minister for law Qamrul Islam and Awami League leader Amir Hossain Amu are scheduled to attend the meeting. Dhaka city Awami League has organised a discussion meeting and a Milad Mahfil at Bangabandhu Avenue at 5pm. Wazed Miah was born on February 16, 1942 in Rangpur. His nickname was Sudha Miah. He married Sheikh Hasina on November 17, 1967. In his early life he joined the Atomic Energy Commission as a physicist and became its chairman before he retired. bdnews24.com/s
